---
/**
 * Category landing page targeting "EHR for therapists" (1,000/mo search volume)
 */
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SoftwareCard from '../components/SoftwareCard.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';

const allSoftware = await getCollection('software');

// Filter and sort for therapist-relevant software
const sortedSoftware = allSoftware
  .map((s) => ({
    ...s.data,
    ketamineFeatureCount: Object.values(s.data.ketamine_features).filter(Boolean).length,
    isTherapistFriendly:
      s.data.pricing.starting_price !== null && s.data.pricing.starting_price < 200,
  }))
  .sort((a, b) => {
    // Prioritize affordable options for solo therapists
    if (a.isTherapistFriendly && !b.isTherapistFriendly) return -1;
    if (!a.isTherapistFriendly && b.isTherapistFriendly) return 1;
    // Then by price (lowest first)
    const priceA = a.pricing.starting_price ?? 999;
    const priceB = b.pricing.starting_price ?? 999;
    return priceA - priceB;
  });

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'CollectionPage',
  name: 'EHR for Therapists 2026',
  description: `Compare ${allSoftware.length} EHR systems designed for therapists. Find affordable practice management software with notes, scheduling, billing, and telehealth.`,
  url: 'https://ketaminesoftware.com/ehr-for-therapists/',
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="EHR for Therapists 2026 - Best Practice Management Software"
  description={`Find the best EHR for therapists in 2026. Compare ${allSoftware.length} practice management systems with therapy notes, scheduling, billing, and telehealth. Prices from $29/mo.`}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <!-- Breadcrumb -->
  <nav class="border-b border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 px-4 py-3 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
      <ol class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
        <li>
          <a href="/" class="text-slate-500 hover:text-slate-700">Home</a>
        </li>
        <li class="text-slate-400">/</li>
        <li class="text-slate-900">EHR for Therapists</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-900 to-slate-800 px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl">
        EHR for Therapists
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-slate-300">
        Find the right electronic health records software for your therapy practice. Compare {allSoftware.length} systems built for mental health professionals.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Intro Content -->
  <section class="px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
        <h2>What Therapists Need in an EHR</h2>
        <p>
          As a therapist, your EHR should simplify your practice, not complicate it. Unlike medical EHRs designed for hospitals, therapy practice software focuses on:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Session notes templates</strong> - SOAP, DAP, and BIRP formats designed for talk therapy</li>
          <li><strong>Simple scheduling</strong> - Online booking, automated reminders, and calendar sync</li>
          <li><strong>Insurance billing</strong> - Claim submission, superbills, and ERA processing</li>
          <li><strong>Secure client portal</strong> - Intake forms, consent documents, and messaging</li>
          <li><strong>Telehealth</strong> - HIPAA-compliant video sessions (essential post-COVID)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We've ranked these EHRs based on ease of use, affordability, and features that matter most to therapists in private practice.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Top Picks -->
  <section class="bg-teal-50 px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Top Picks for Therapists</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-teal-200 bg-white p-6">
          <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-teal-100 px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-teal-700">Best Overall</span>
          <h3 class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">SimplePractice</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Most popular choice with 250,000+ users. Intuitive interface, great telehealth.</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-lg font-semibold text-teal-600">From $49/mo</p>
          <a href="/software/simplepractice/" class="mt-4 inline-block text-sm text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-700">Read review →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6">
          <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-slate-700">Best Value</span>
          <h3 class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">TheraNest</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Most affordable option with AI-enhanced notes. Great for new practices.</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-lg font-semibold text-teal-600">From $29/mo</p>
          <a href="/software/theranest/" class="mt-4 inline-block text-sm text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-700">Read review →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6">
          <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-slate-700">Best for Groups</span>
          <h3 class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">TherapyNotes</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Robust billing and scheduling. Scales well for group practices.</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-lg font-semibold text-teal-600">From $49/mo</p>
          <a href="/software/therapynotes/" class="mt-4 inline-block text-sm text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-700">Read review →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- All Software Grid -->
  <section class="px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">All EHR Options for Therapists</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
        Sorted by price - most affordable first
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {sortedSoftware.map((software) => (
          <SoftwareCard
            name={software.name}
            slug={software.slug}
            description={software.description}
            logo={software.logo}
            startingPrice={software.pricing.starting_price}
            currency={software.pricing.currency}
            pricingModel={software.pricing.model}
            hasFreeTrisl={software.pricing.has_free_trial}
            ketamineFeatureCount={software.ketamineFeatureCount}
            isKetamineSpecific={software.isTherapistFriendly}
          />
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="bg-slate-50 px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Common Questions</h2>
      <div class="mt-8 space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Do I really need an EHR for my therapy practice?</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
            If you accept insurance or plan to scale your practice, yes. EHRs streamline billing, reduce paperwork, and help maintain HIPAA compliance. Even cash-pay practices benefit from automated scheduling and telehealth.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">What's the cheapest EHR for therapists?</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
            TheraNest starts at $29/month and includes the essentials. SimplePractice starts at $49/month with more features. Both offer free trials.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Is SimplePractice worth the cost?</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
            SimplePractice is the most popular choice among therapists for good reason - intuitive interface, reliable telehealth, and strong community support. At $49-99/month, most therapists find the time savings worth the investment.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Can I use a free EHR for my therapy practice?</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
            Practice Fusion offers a free EHR option, but it's designed for medical practices, not therapy. For therapy-specific workflows, paid options like TheraNest ($29/mo) provide better value.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Compare Side-by-Side</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">
        Not sure which EHR is right for you? Compare any two systems feature-by-feature.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/compare/"
        class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-teal-600 px-6 py-3 text-base font-medium text-white hover:bg-teal-700"
      >
        Compare EHR Software
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
